verbose_text: A normal beta-tryptase level equates to elevation of inactive protryptase and a baseline higher MC burdern.6, 10 An elevated beta-tryptase level indicates that MCs were recently activated and released beta-tryptase (the half-life of tryptase is on the order of two to four hours).18 Our patient had an elevated total serum tryptase level and a normal beta-tryptase level.
